---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="SolarROI — Branded solar proposals from your iPhone">
  <header
    class="border-b border-solar-hairline bg-white/80 backdrop-blur sticky top-0 z-10"
  >
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 h-16 flex items-center justify-between">
      <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2 font-bold tracking-tight">
        <span
          class="inline-block w-3 h-3 rounded-sm bg-solar-orange"
          aria-hidden="true"></span>
        SolarROI
      </a>
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-6 text-sm text-solar-muted">
        <a href="#features" class="hover:text-solar-ink">Features</a>
        <a href="#demo" class="hover:text-solar-ink">Demo</a>
        <a href="#waitlist" class="hover:text-solar-ink">Waitlist</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <!-- HERO -->
    <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 pt-20 pb-16 sm:pt-28 sm:pb-24">
      <p
        class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-solar-orange mb-4"
      >
        For solar contractors
      </p>
      <h1
        class="text-4xl sm:text-6xl font-extrabold tracking-tight leading-[1.05] max-w-3xl"
      >
        Branded solar proposals,
        <span class="text-solar-orange">in minutes.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-solar-muted max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
        SolarROI turns an address and a few system specs into a polished,
        NREL-backed PDF proposal — complete with production estimates, ITC, and
        payback. Built for the field, runs on your iPhone.
      </p>

      <!--
        TODO (App Store launch): replace this email form with the official
        App Store badge once SolarROI is live.
        e.g. <a href="https://apps.apple.com/app/idXXXXXXXXX">
               <img src="/app-store-badge.svg" alt="Download on the App Store" />
             </a>
      -->
      <div id="waitlist" class="mt-10 max-w-xl">
        <form
          action="https://buttondown.email/api/emails/embed-subscribe/SOLARROI_USERNAME"
          method="post"
          target="popupwindow"
          onsubmit="window.open('https://buttondown.email/SOLARROI_USERNAME', 'popupwindow')"
          class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3"
        >
          <!-- TODO: replace SOLARROI_USERNAME (in both action and onsubmit) with the real Buttondown handle once the account exists. -->
          <label for="bd-email" class="sr-only">Email address</label>
          <input
            id="bd-email"
            type="email"
            name="email"
            required
            placeholder="you@yoursolarco.com"
            class="flex-1 h-12 px-4 rounded-lg border border-solar-hairline focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-solar-orange focus:border-solar-orange bg-white"
          />
          <button
            type="submit"
            class="h-12 px-6 rounded-lg bg-solar-orange text-white font-semibold hover:opacity-90 transition"
          >
            Join the waitlist
          </button>
        </form>
        <div class="mt-4 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-solar-muted">
          <a
            href="#demo"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 hover:text-solar-ink"
          >
            <svg
              width="14"
              height="14"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              fill="currentColor"
              aria-hidden="true"
            >
              <path d="M8 5v14l11-7z"></path>
            </svg>
            Watch demo
          </a>
          <span class="text-solar-hairline">·</span>
          <span>No spam. Launch updates only.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FEATURES -->
    <section id="features" class="bg-solar-orange/[0.04] border-y border-solar-hairline">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
        <p
          class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-solar-orange mb-3"
        >
          What it does
        </p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight max-w-2xl">
          Everything a contractor needs to quote a job — nothing they don't.
        </h2>

        <div class="mt-12 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
          <div
            class="rounded-xl border border-solar-hairline bg-white p-6 flex flex-col"
          >
            <div
              class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-solar-orange/10 text-solar-orange flex items-center justify-center mb-4 font-semibold"
            >
              kW
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg">PVWatts-backed estimates</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-solar-muted leading-relaxed">
              Production numbers come straight from NREL's PVWatts v8 — the
              same engine the industry trusts. Address geocoding happens
              on-device via Apple Maps.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="rounded-xl border border-solar-hairline bg-white p-6 flex flex-col"
          >
            <div
              class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-solar-orange/10 text-solar-orange flex items-center justify-center mb-4 font-semibold"
            >
              PDF
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg">Branded PDF proposals</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-solar-muted leading-relaxed">
              Generate a clean, client-ready proposal with your company info,
              system design, ITC, and 25-year savings — ready to AirDrop or
              email.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="rounded-xl border border-solar-hairline bg-white p-6 flex flex-col"
          >
            <div
              class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-solar-orange/10 text-solar-orange flex items-center justify-center mb-4 font-semibold"
            >
              ☰
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg">Project library</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-solar-muted leading-relaxed">
              Every project is saved locally on your device. Pick up where you
              left off, duplicate a job, or iterate on a quote without
              starting over.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="rounded-xl border border-solar-hairline bg-white p-6 flex flex-col"
          >
            <div
              class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-solar-orange/10 text-solar-orange flex items-center justify-center mb-4 font-semibold"
            >
              ★
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg">Pro: $4.99/mo</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-solar-muted leading-relaxed">
              Unlimited projects · Watermark-free PDFs · upload your own
              watermark image. Free tier supports 3 projects with a SolarROI
              watermark.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- DEMO -->
    <section id="demo" class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
      <p
        class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-solar-orange mb-3"
      >
        See it in action
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">
        From address to proposal in under two minutes.
      </h2>

      <div
        class="mt-10 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden border border-solar-hairline bg-solar-ink/[0.03] aspect-video flex items-center justify-center relative"
      >
        {/* TODO: drop the recorded screen capture into /public/demo.mp4
            and (optionally) /public/demo-poster.jpg. The <video> tag below
            will pick them up automatically. The onerror handler reveals the
            "Demo coming soon" overlay if /demo.mp4 isn't there yet. */}
        <video
          class="w-full h-full object-cover"
          controls
          playsinline
          preload="metadata"
          poster="/demo-poster.jpg"
          onerror="this.style.display='none'; document.getElementById('demo-fallback').style.display='flex';"
        >
          <source src="/demo.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
        </video>
        <div
          id="demo-fallback"
          class="absolute inset-0 hidden flex-col items-center justify-center text-center px-6 text-solar-muted"
        >
          <div
            class="w-14 h-14 rounded-full bg-solar-orange/10 text-solar-orange flex items-center justify-center mb-4"
          >
            <svg
              width="22"
              height="22"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              fill="currentColor"
              aria-hidden="true"
            >
              <path d="M8 5v14l11-7z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-solar-ink">Demo coming soon</p>
          <p class="text-sm mt-1">
            We're polishing the walkthrough. Join the waitlist to get notified.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHO IT'S FOR -->
    <section class="border-t border-solar-hairline">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2 items-start">
        <div>
          <p
            class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] uppercase text-solar-orange mb-3"
          >
            Who it's for
          </p>
          <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">
            Built for solar contractors who close deals on the roof — not at a
            desk.
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="text-solar-muted leading-relaxed space-y-4 text-lg">
          <p>
            If you're an installer, sales rep, or independent contractor sick
            of bouncing between spreadsheets, web tools, and a desktop CAD
            package just to hand a homeowner a number — SolarROI is for you.
          </p>
          <p>
            Set your contractor profile once (company, license, contact, logo)
            and every proposal you generate is automatically branded as
            yours. Inputs are simple: address, system size, tilt, azimuth,
            roof type. The math and the formatting are handled.
          </p>
          <p class="text-solar-ink font-medium">
            One person. One iPhone. One proposal in the homeowner's inbox
            before you leave the driveway.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CLOSING CTA -->
    <section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
      <div
        class="rounded-2xl bg-solar-ink text-white p-10 sm:p-14 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center justify-between gap-6"
      >
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">
            Be first in line when SolarROI ships.
          </h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-white/70">
            Coming to the App Store soon. Join the waitlist for launch
            pricing.
          </p>
        </div>
        <a
          href="#waitlist"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center h-12 px-6 rounded-lg bg-solar-orange text-white font-semibold hover:opacity-90 transition whitespace-nowrap"
        >
          Join the waitlist
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
